Generated the Ui Color developer guide at `output/ui-color.md`. The document covers:

- **Creating UiColor Values**: RGBA constructors, Vector4 conversion, hex RGB notation, and default construction
- **Theme Color Identifiers**: String-based color IDs, predefined constants (PRIMARY, BACKGROUND, OUTLINE), and ID inspection methods
- **Alpha Manipulation**: `WithAlpha()` and `ScaleAlpha()` methods with fluent chaining support
- **Retrieving Color Values**: `GetRgba()`, implicit Vector4 conversion, and copy/move semantics

All API examples were verified against the public header (`repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/public-api/ui-color.h`) and UTC test cases (`repos/dali-ui/automated-tests/src/dali-ui-foundation/utc-Dali-UiColor.cpp`).
